04:17.252 --> 04:31.350
So I think that, in general, the notion that the 
ocean is a great reservoir of protein is, with the

04:17.252 --> 04:31.350
present fishing techniques, is just not so.

04:34.199 --> 04:36.702
our great reservoir of food supply. Of course, 
food, we need millions of it. We need something

04:38.784 --> 04:54.202
like the total requirement right now is something 
like a billion, 200 million, 300 million, about a

04:38.784 --> 04:54.202
billion and a half million, a billion, 500 million 
tons of food, mostly for calories.

05:01.230 --> 05:02.772
But by the development of of ocean farming, we 
might be able to increase this

05:04.051 --> 05:18.471
production of things that people like and need 
maybe several fold over. And the interesting

05:18.512 --> 05:25.321
thing about ocean farming is that you do it in a 
different way than you do it on land. The best

05:25.722 --> 05:31.250
example is the mussel farming that the Spaniards 
do. They get about 100 tons to the acre of mussels

05:35.135 --> 05:39.562
maybe 20 tons to the acre of protein, which is 
fantastically high. The reason that they're able

05:40.724 --> 05:52.684
to do this is that they put their muscles on ropes or 
pilings, but mostly ropes, I think, in an area

05:40.724 --> 05:52.684
where the current constantly sweeps by them. So 
that the ocean is fertilizing itself. You're

05:57.031 --> 06:01.058
taking advantage of the organic production in a 
large part of the ocean. sweeping by these

06:01.780 --> 06:05.866
mussels, and the mussels all you do is just filter 
it out of the water as it goes by. That's why you get

06:07.348 --> 06:08.710
these high yields. And that's the way to do marine 
farming, I think, not to take a piece of ocean and

06:08.750 --> 06:15.579
fertilize it. Might as well just use ordinary 
agriculture for that. But to take advantage of the

06:19.225 --> 06:31.602
oceans, of the motions of the ocean, to make the 
ocean fertilize itself, and to

06:19.225 --> 06:31.602
bring nutrients to a small area. from which you 
then get a large crop.

06:41.972 --> 06:50.885
And I think that the energy requirements here are 
rather low.

06:50.945 --> 07:01.740
The energy requirements are primarily catching 
and handling, not so much energy for fertilizer or

06:50.945 --> 07:01.740
energy for plowing or energy for pumping water. 
the ocean will do all that for you. You have to catch

07:05.425 --> 07:06.808
the mussels. You have to hang them there. You have 
to pull them up and take them out of their shells and

07:09.171 --> 07:15.722
then do something with them. I would think 
particularly of mariculture of organisms like

07:15.742 --> 07:25.939
mussels, oysters, clams, and mussels, which are 
filter feeders. therefore can collect are just

07:26.932 --> 07:38.365
essentially little plankton nets, convert the 
plankton into something we like to eat, seafood.

